Protiva Bose (also spelled Pratibha Basu; Bengali: প্রতিভা বসু) (March 13, 1915 – 13 October 2006) was a singer and one of the most prolific and widely read Bengali writers of novels, short stories, and essays.
She was born in a village near Dhaka in 1915 to Asutosh Shome and Sarajubala Shome.
She was known as Ranu Shome before she married the Bengali writer, Buddhadev Bose in 1934.
She had two daughters, Meenakshi Dutta and Damayanti Basu Singh, and a son, Suddhasil Bose, who died at the age of 42.
